This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category. The paper also proposes a new loss function for training deep neural networks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its approach on two popular face recognition benchmarks, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography (cs.CR) aspects.
